# Source of truth for what the overlay image does NOT ship.
#
# The Dockerfile is a single ``COPY . /overlay`` (matching upstream's
# canonical pattern in .centaur/docs/public/md/extend/overlay.md:80-84),
# so anything we want to keep out of the runtime payload must be
# excluded here.
#
# Build context is the repo root (post-ACME-mirror reorg). Everything that
# is NOT an overlay extension point (tools/, workflows/, .agents/, services/)
# must be excluded explicitly.

# Version control
.git
.gitmodules
.github

# Submodules — vendored upstream source trees, never shipped in the
# overlay image. ``.centaur`` is the base platform; ``.scientist`` is
# AI-Scientist-v2 (the BFTS reference implementation we port from).
# ``centaur_sdk`` is a dev-only repo-root symlink into
# ``.centaur/centaur_sdk`` (see pyproject.toml); the API pod has its
# own ``/app/centaur_sdk/`` so the overlay must not ship one.
.centaur
.scientist
centaur_sdk

# Dev/ops directories at the repo root that aren't part of the overlay.
# ``db``, ``clusters``, ``infra``, ``cloudflared``, and ``docs`` were
# deleted post-reorg but are kept here as defense-in-depth so a stray
# local re-creation doesn't silently bloat the image.
db
cloudflared
docs
clusters
infra
.cursor
.worktrees

# Helm values + GitOps configs (consumed at deploy time, not runtime).
values*.yaml

# Virtual environments
**/.venv

# Caches
**/__pycache__
**/.pytest_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/*.pyc

# Lock files (root ``pyproject.toml`` is the dev-venv source of
# truth; deploy-time deps live in the API pod image, not the overlay).
**/*.lock

# Docker
.dockerignore

# Tests (root pytest suite + tool / workflow test trees never run inside
# the API or sandbox pods)
tests
**/tests
tmp

# Environment (secrets — never bake into images)
**/.env
**/.env.*

# Non-runtime markdown.
#
# Most ``*.md`` files are README-style developer docs that don't belong
# in the image, but a few are runtime payload that the API/sandbox
# explicitly reads at request time. Allow-list those:
#
#   - ``.agents/skills/**`` — every skill is a ``SKILL.md`` plus its
#     reference docs; the sandbox loads them when the agent invokes a
#     skill.
#   - ``services/**/SYSTEM_PROMPT.md`` — overlay prompt overlays live
#     next to the upstream service they extend (see
#     .centaur/docs/public/md/extend/overlay.md:32-34). Scoped to the
#     exact filename so other developer-doc ``*.md`` files under
#     ``services/`` (READMEs, runbooks) stay out of the runtime image.
*.md
!.agents/skills/**
!services/**/SYSTEM_PROMPT.md
